I need a way to external containers to say "hey docker, that container is unhealthy" and eventually ask docker to kill it __eou__
regardless what docker or the container itself think __eou__
this pattern is common in distributed computing actually... __eou__
K8s, Rancher, Swarm __eou__
Take what you need they all check for that __eou__
you mean they check themselves, not the containers __eou__

K8s and Rancher has healthchecks for their "services" and swarm simply checks that all containers have a healthy state. And as long as every container has a healty state all containers work as expected and everything from outside is L4 mesh magic :D __eou__

i think he's saying they check the container's health status based on the result of that HEALTHCHECK entry as likely listed bydocker inspect, and have an option to auto-kill the container should it be unhealthy __eou__

There are 2 types of health check. Local, where if unhealthy, just suicide(the HEALTHCHECK is a good candidate for that) and the distributed consensus, which is made by external sources trying to reach that container and failing, so they agree on ask docker to kill it __eou__
In orleans case the consensus is what I'm having problems to implement in docker due to those limitations __eou__
The self check can be made with the HEALTHCHECK just fine I guess __eou__
